{"id": "food_FOOD00809", "name": "Rye bread (food medium)", "category": "food", "organism_scope": "food microbiome / general", "aerobic": true, "description": "Food-derived medium: metabolizable components of Rye bread [Cereals and cereal products] from FooDB, plus a standard M9 mineral base. Organic components use presence-based uptake bounds; FooDB content retained. Measured compounds with no BiGG exchange are listed under uncovered.", "namespace": "bigg", "provenance": {"source_type": "database", "citation": "FooDB v2020-04-07 (Wishart DS et al., foodb.ca). Content sources: DTU, PHENOL EXPLORER, USDA.", "doi": "", "url": "https://foodb.ca/downloads", "notes": "Organic components mapped from FooDB compounds to BiGG via InChIKey/name. Mineral base added. Bounds presence-based; foodb_content retained. Unmapped measured compounds kept in uncovered (v2 completeness fix). IMPORTANT: composition values are taken from the archived FooDB 2020-04-07 CSV data release; FooDB's live food page no longer displays this bulk composition, so it will appear empty. Verify individual compounds via the per-component cross-reference links. Underlying content was aggregated by FooDB from USDA / DTU / Phenol Explorer.", "data_release": "FooDB 2020-04-07 CSV release (foodb.ca/downloads)", "food_record": "https://foodb.ca/foods/FOOD00809", "verification": "expert-curated (multi-source food composition; growth-relevant profile completed, FooDB noise removed)", "curation_date": "2026-07-17", "curation_sources": ["USDA FoodData Central FDC 172684 (Bread, rye) - full nutrient panel: macros, sugars, 18 amino acids, minerals, vitamins, fatty acids", "Scald fermentation rye bread, Foods/Nutrients 2025, PMC11941048 - sugars (maltose 12-13% dw, glucose/fructose/sucrose) and organic acids (lactic 0.81-2.06, acetic 0.16-0.23, succinic 0.03-0.17 g/100g dw)", "LAB starter wholemeal rye bread, PMC8759695 - lactic/acetic acid and fermentation quotient", "FODMAP fingerprinting of bakery products & sourdoughs, PMC8074121 - fructose, FOS/fructans, mannitol in rye and rye sourdough", "Sourdough organic-acid survey ranges (lactic 0.22-0.87, acetic 0.07-0.10 g/100g fw)", "FooDB FOOD00809 (Rye bread) - base record and phenolic/alkylresorcinol coverage"], "curation_notes": "Dominant carbon/energy sources are STARCH (~39 g/100g) and its hydrolysis product MALTOSE (~2.5 g/100g, the main residual free sugar after yeast/LAB fermentation); LACTIC ACID (~0.6 g/100g, added here - was missing) is the defining sourdough metabolite and a key organic-acid carbon source, with acetic and succinic acids from heterofermentative LAB. Sugar split is anchored to the measured USDA total sugars (3.8 g/100g) with maltose-dominant proportions from rye-bread HPLC literature; organic acid", "curation_added": ["lactic acid (dominant sourdough organic acid, ~0.6 g/100g) - absent from FooDB record", "acetic acid (~0.15 g/100g) - absent from FooDB record", "succinic acid (~0.05 g/100g) - absent from FooDB record", "maltose apportioned as the dominant free sugar (~2.5 g/100g within USDA total sugars 3.8)", "quantitative amounts for all sugars, amino acids, minerals, vitamins, fatty acids from USDA FDC 172684", "mannitol (rye-sourdough LAB fermentation product; present but unquantified in baked bread)", "explicit starch amount (~38.7 g/100g) as the dominant carbon source", "L-serine to replace the D-serine artifact"], "curation_removed": [{"name": "Cyanocobalamin", "reason": "vitamin B12 = 0 in unfortified plant/cereal bread (USDA FDC 172684 B12 = 0); not synthesised by rye"}, {"name": "Retinol", "reason": "preformed vitamin A (animal-derived) = 0 in rye bread (USDA vitamin A = 0); implausible"}, {"name": "Beta-Carotene", "reason": "USDA vitamin A / carotene = 0 for rye bread; negligible/absent, FooDB predicted"}, {"name": "Beta-Cryptoxanthin", "reason": "carotenoid absent in rye bread (USDA vitamin A = 0); FooDB predicted noise"}, {"name": "Fe2+ mitochondria", "reason": "model-compartment artifact - duplicate of iron; a food has no mitochondrial Fe pool"}, {"name": "Iron (Fe3+)", "reason": "redundant duplicate iron entry; consolidated into single 'iron' value"}, {"name": "D-Serine", "reason": "non-biological enantiomer; protein-derived serine is L-serine (replaced by L-serine)"}, {"name": "Nickel", "reason": "non-nutritive trace contaminant, not a growth nutrient of bread"}, {"name": "Chromium", "reason": "non-nutritive ultratrace element; not a quantified rye-bread nutrient, FooDB noise"}, {"name": "Co2+", "reason": "free cobalt ion - ultratrace/contaminant; no B12 pathway in plant bread to make it a nutrient"}, {"name": "Vaccenic acid", "reason": "18:1 n-7 trans/ruminant fatty acid; implausible in cereal lipid, FooDB predicted"}, {"name": "Gadoleic acid", "reason": "20:1 fatty acid; not a component of rye/wheat lipid (USDA reports no 20:1), FooDB predicted noise"}, {"name": "Hexanoate (n-C6:0)", "reason": "medium-chain fatty acid absent in cereal lipid; FooDB predicted noise"}, {"name": "Octanoic acid", "reason": "C8:0 medium-chain fatty acid absent in rye/wheat lipid; FooDB predicted noise"}, {"name": "Nonanoate", "reason": "C9:0 fatty acid; not a rye-bread lipid component, FooDB predicted noise"}, {"name": "Decanoic acid", "reason": "C10:0 medium-chain fatty acid absent in cereal lipid; FooDB predicted noise"}, {"name": "Dodecanoic acid", "reason": "lauric acid (C12:0) absent in rye/wheat lipid; FooDB predicted noise"}, {"name": "(R)-Oxypeucedanin", "reason": "furanocoumarin of Apiaceae/citrus; biologically implausible in rye bread, FooDB mis-assignment"}], "curation_confidence": "high"}, "components": [{"name": "starch", "bigg_metabolite": "starch", "exchange": "EX_starch_e", "lower_bound": -10.0, "upper_bound": 1000.0, "concentration_mM": null, "xref": {"kegg": "C00369", "chebi": "CHEBI:14687", "kegg_drug": "D00084", "kegg_glycan": "G10545", "biocyc": "META:CPD-8556", "mnx": "MNXM1103451", "seed": "cpd11657", "formula": "C12H20O10*2"}, "in_biggr": true, "e